# Tailwind CSS v4 Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- CSS-first configuration in v4 (no `tailwind.config.js`)
- Define design tokens with `@theme` directive in CSS
- Use `@layer` for component styles that need utility overriding
- Use `@apply` sparingly — prefer utility classes directly

## Best Practices
- DO: Use semantic class grouping: layout → spacing → typography → colors → effects
- DO: Use arbitrary values `[value]` when design tokens don't cover the case
- DO: Use responsive prefixes mobile-first: `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- DO: Use `dark:` variant for dark mode support
- DON'T: Create 20+ utilities on a single element — extract a component
- DON'T: Use `@apply` for everything — defeats the purpose of utility-first

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first: base styles → `sm:` → `md:` → `lg:` → `xl:` → `2xl:`
- Use container queries `@container` for component-level responsiveness
- Use `max-*` variants for max-width breakpoints

## Modern Features (v4)
- Use CSS variables for dynamic theming
- Use `@variant` for custom variants
- Use `color-mix()` for dynamic color adjustments
- Use `has-*:` and `group-has-*:` for parent-based styling
- Use `*:` variant for styling direct children

## Component Extraction
- Extract repeated patterns into components, not `@apply` classes
- Use `cn()` / `clsx()` for conditional class merging
- Keep utility strings readable with consistent ordering
